&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a Senior Infrastructure Projects Engineer to join our dynamic Infrastructure Projects team. This team is dedicated to managing a range of initiatives, from large-scale build-outs and relocation projects to targeted infrastructure service improvements.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a client-facing engineer, you will regularly interact with C-suite stakeholders, translating complex technical concepts into clear, actionable communication, and expectation setting is imperative. The location options for this role are: Boston, CA Bay Area, or New York, with frequent local travel required within the greater region surrounding those areas. Occasional travel to other Pliancy hubs may be necessary.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What is the work like?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Many of our clients are showing consistent growth. This manifests as a lot of movement into and out of office spaces. In both of our client verticals, we find ourselves:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Joining owner, architect, and contractor calls to work closely with construction teams and their subcontractors for pieces that impact low-voltage and audiovisual installations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Designing, ordering, and implementing a full network stack (switching, firewalls, and wireless).&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partnering with internet service providers and working with them from site surveys to circuit activation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Scoping and installing AV hardware for high-traffic conference rooms, executive suites, and hybrid collaboration spaces&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There is a lot of on-site work, but there will be instances where you are doing various, remote value-add efforts (predictive wireless surveys, license renewals, maintenance, or post-installation support).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who are we looking for?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our ideal candidate has a strong technical background with a project manager’s mindset&lt;strong&gt;.&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;You are someone who finds as much satisfaction in an organized server rack and a flawlessly executed office move as you do in troubleshooting a complex routing issue.&amp;nbsp;You are able to communicate effectively with both technical and non-technical stakeholders.In addition to managing day-to-day operations, you will help play a key role in maintaining and continuously improving our standards. You are a &quot;T-shaped&quot; engineer: you possess expertise in Network Architecture (Layer 2/3) and Physical Infrastructure, supplemented by a broad understanding of the modern SaaS/IaaS and AV stacks. You don&#39;t just follow a project plan—you help build the standards that define how Pliancy executes infrastructure work.&lt;/p&gt;
